# Misc follow-ups

Rolling notes that don't warrant a dedicated doc. Completed items are
dropped once they land; keep this file lean.

## Parsing / gen bugs to revisit

- `IPython.lib.display.audio` — bullet list in parameters parse check.
- `numpy.core.shape_base._concatenate_shapes` — parse + completeness
  review.
- `numpy.errstate` — fields alternate between `numpy._ErrDict` /
  `numpy.dict`; pick one canonical.
- `numpy.histogram_bin_edges` — block-math in
  `_content.Notes.children.2.children.0.dd` and math not rendered.
- `scipy.sparse.data._create_method.<locals>.method` — canonical-name
  conflict with an unrelated `tan`/`float`.

## Papyri bugs surfaced running against IPython 9.12 / numpy 2.4 on Py 3.14

### PEP 649 / lazy-annotations compat in `papyri/signature.py`

`ObjectSignature.from_str` builds the target via `exec()` on a `def`
string with an empty globals dict, then calls `inspect.signature` on
it. On Python 3.14, annotations are evaluated lazily in those empty
globals, so any name the signature string references (`Any`,
`collections`, `t_total`, …) raises `NameError` at
`inspect.signature()` time.

Reproduces on `IPython.core.oinspect:OInfo`,
`IPython.terminal.shortcuts:Binding/BaseBinding/RuntimeBinding`,
`IPython.utils.timing:clock2/timings/timings_out`.

**Fix sketch:** on Py 3.14+, call
`inspect.signature(target_item, annotation_format=annotationlib.Format.STRING)`
(or `FORWARDREF`) so names stay unresolved; or seed a richer globals
dict; or catch `NameError` and fall back to stringified annotations.

### `AssertionError` in `papyri/ts.py:468`

`assert len(post_text) >= len(self.as_text(tc))` fires on numpy dtype
classes whose docstring starts with a short signature line followed by
a `--` underline shorter than the title — tree-sitter-rst reads that as
a section header. Affects ~25 entries: `numpy:dtype`, `numpy.fft:fft`,
and all of `numpy.dtypes:*DType`.

**Fix:** loosen the assert to a logged soft-fail, or detect the
"too-short adornment" case earlier and treat the first line as a
signature instead of a title.

## Upstream docstring issues worth reporting

- `numpy.random._mt19937:MT19937._legacy_seeding` has unbalanced
  backticks (```` `SeedSequence, or ``None` ````) in `_mt19937.pyx`;
  triggers papyri's "Improper backtick" warning 3×.
- `numpy.polynomial._polybase:ABCPolyBase` uses a `Class Attributes`
  section that numpydoc (and our `numpydoc_compat.NumpyDocString`)
  doesn't recognise. Either add the alias or ask numpy to switch to a
  canonical section name.
- `IPython.utils.timing:{clock2,timings,timings_out}` carry a
  non-signature first line with tuple-literal return annotations
  (`-> (t_user, t_system)`). Really a papyri problem (see PEP 649
  bullet) but IPython could drop the synopsis line now that real
  annotations exist.

## Linting / stability tooling — queued

Extra type checkers (`ty`, `pyrefly`) intentionally excluded.

### Ruff rule expansion
- Expand `[tool.ruff.lint] select` with `SIM`, `RUF`, `PERF`,
  `PIE`, `RET`, and a `PL` subset. `B`, `I`, `UP` already on. Land
  autofixes as a separate commit per rule group.

### Test stability
- `pytest-xdist` for parallel execution.
- `pytest-randomly` to shuffle order (guards against import-order
  latent bugs).
- `pytest-timeout` with a global ceiling so gen-adjacent tests can't
  hang CI.
- Golden-file test: `papyri gen examples/papyri.toml --no-infer` then
  assert expected files exist + decode as CBOR.
- `papyri describe` smoke test against the self-generated bundle.

### Security / supply chain
- `pip-audit` step in CI.
- `bandit` scoped to `papyri/gen.py` (runs example code); accept
  noisiness and tune rules.
- Dependabot / Renovate for GitHub Actions pins.

### Mypy
- Tighten `[tool.mypy]`: `warn_unused_ignores`, `warn_redundant_casts`,
  `no_implicit_optional`, `check_untyped_defs`. Full `strict` is too
  invasive for the IR code.

### Pre-commit
- `.pre-commit-config.yaml` with `ruff check --fix`, `ruff format`,
  `mypy`, `check-added-large-files`.

### CI hygiene
- `permissions: contents: read` on each workflow.
- `concurrency:` + `cancel-in-progress: true` on PR workflows.
- `zizmor` to lint Actions YAML for injection-prone `${{ }}` usage.
